cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image compression and its impact on computer vision tasks such as object detection and segmentation. 
2) cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper deals with lossy image compression, which is a common multimedia application. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for image compression. 
4) cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper deals with evaluating image compression techniques using a new metric learned on perceptual similarity data. 
5) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel end-to-end trainable model for image compression that incorporates object saliency and a deep perceptual loss.
